text: Now that the TEL MRT station is up, they've also revamped the entire space to be much more conducive for travellers. I really like that it's a huge bus stop, and it's extremely handicapped friendly. Lifts, escalators, ramps, are all built up here, especially since they're servicing users of Gleneagles Hospital across the road.
Very small, hot and humid. Sheltered but doesn't seem to a good area if heavy rain. Surrounding under construction, dusty and dirty
The surrounding area is under construction
